# Banking API — Final 2026 SWE Roadmap

## Architecture Decisions

| Decision | Choice | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Data access | EF Core `DbContext` directly (no Repository wrapper) | `DbContext` IS already a Unit of Work; `DbSet<T>` IS a Repository. Wrapping adds boilerplate, not value. |
| API style | **Controllers + Minimal APIs** (learn both) | Controllers for complex endpoints; Minimal APIs for simple ones. Both are first-class in .NET 10. |
| Database | **SQL Server Express** (upgrade from SQLite) | The natural C#/.NET database; free, production-realistic, what .NET hiring managers expect |
| Orchestration | **Docker Compose → .NET Aspire** | Aspire auto-wires services and adds observability for free |
| Testing | xUnit + FluentAssertions + WebApplicationFactory | Industry standard combo for .NET |
| Frontend | React + TypeScript | Most in-demand full-stack combo |
| Auth | ASP.NET Core Identity API Endpoints | Built-in, modern, no manual JWT code |

