## Phase 8 — Docker, .NET Aspire, CI/CD & Azure

> Ship it to the real world.

| Task | Skill Learned |
|---|---|
| Multi-stage Dockerfile (build stage → tiny runtime image) | Container optimization |
| Docker Compose: API + React + SQL Server | Multi-container orchestration |
| **.NET Aspire** orchestration (auto-wires services + adds observability) | Cloud-native .NET |
| GitHub Actions: build → test → Docker image on every push | CI/CD pipeline |
| Deploy to **Azure App Service** (free tier) | Cloud deployment |
| Professional README: architecture diagram, badges, screenshots | Documentation |

> **.NET Aspire** is the 2024+ replacement for hand-written Docker Compose in .NET apps. It auto-discovers services, adds health checks, and provides a dashboard for distributed tracing.

> **Why SQL Server Express?** It's the natural pair for C#/.NET, free, and what .NET job postings expect. EF Core abstracts the DB — switching to PostgreSQL later takes 5 minutes (just swap one NuGet package).

